file.name: googleapis.com-adexchangeseller-v1.1-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  contact:
    name: Google
    url: https://google.com
  description: Accesses the inventory of Ad Exchange seller users and generates reports.
  title: Ad Exchange Seller
  version: v1.1
  x-apiClientRegistration:
    url: https://console.developers.google.com
  x-logo:
    url: https://www.doubleclickbygoogle.com/static/core/img/doubleclick-google-logo-wide.svg
  x-origin:
    - converter:
        url: https://github.com/lucybot/api-spec-converter
        version: 2.7.11
      format: google
      url: https://www.googleapis.com/discovery/v1/apis/adexchangeseller/v1.1/rest
      version: v1
  x-preferred: false
  x-providerName: googleapis.com
  x-serviceName: adexchangeseller
externalDocs:
  url: https://developers.google.com/ad-exchange/seller-rest/
tags:
  - name: accounts
  - name: adclients
  - name: adunits
  - name: alerts
  - name: customchannels
  - name: metadata
  - name: preferreddeals
  - name: reports
  - name: urlchannels
paths:
  "/accounts/{accountId}":
    get:
      description: Get information about the selected Ad Exchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.accounts.get
      parameters:
        - description: "Account to get information about. Tip: 'myaccount' is a valid ID."
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Account"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /adclients:
    get:
      description: List all ad clients in this Ad Exchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.adclients.list
      parameters:
        - description: The maximum number of ad clients to include in the response, used
            for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad clients. To retrieve
            the next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken"
            from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdClients"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - adclients
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits":
    get:
      description: List all ad units in the specified ad client for this Ad Exchange
        account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.adunits.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client for which to list ad units.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: "Whether to include inactive ad units. Default: true."
          in: query
          name: includeInactive
          schema:
            type: boolean
        - description: The maximum number of ad units to include in the response, used for
            paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad units. To retrieve the
            next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken" from
            the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnits"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - adunits
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits/{adUnitId}":
    get:
      description: Gets the specified ad unit in the specified ad client.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.adunits.get
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client for which to get the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit to retrieve.
          in: path
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - adunits
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits/{adUnitId}/customchannels":
    get:
      description: List all custom channels which the specified ad unit belongs to.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.adunits.customchannels.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client which contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit for which to list custom channels.
          in: path
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of custom channels to include in the response,
            used for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through custom channels. To
            retrieve the next page, set this parameter to the value of
            "nextPageToken" from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannels"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - adunits
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/customchannels":
    get:
      description: List all custom channels in the specified ad client for this Ad Exchange
        account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.customchannels.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client for which to list custom channels.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of custom channels to include in the response,
            used for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through custom channels. To
            retrieve the next page, set this parameter to the value of
            "nextPageToken" from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannels"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - customchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/customchannels/{customChannelId}":
    get:
      description: Get the specified custom channel from the specified ad client.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.customchannels.get
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client which contains the custom channel.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Custom channel to retrieve.
          in: path
          name: customChannelId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - customchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/customchannels/{customChannelId}/adunits":
    get:
      description: List all ad units in the specified custom channel.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.customchannels.adunits.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client which contains the custom channel.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Custom channel for which to list ad units.
          in: path
          name: customChannelId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: "Whether to include inactive ad units. Default: true."
          in: query
          name: includeInactive
          schema:
            type: boolean
        - description: The maximum number of ad units to include in the response, used for
            paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad units. To retrieve the
            next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken" from
            the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnits"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - customchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/urlchannels":
    get:
      description: List all URL channels in the specified ad client for this Ad Exchange
        account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.urlchannels.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client for which to list URL channels.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of URL channels to include in the response, used
            for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through URL channels. To retrieve
            the next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken"
            from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/UrlChannels"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - urlchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /alerts:
    get:
      description: List the alerts for this Ad Exchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.alerts.list
      parameters:
        - description: The locale to use for translating alert messages. The account locale
            will be used if this is not supplied. The AdSense default (English)
            will be used if the supplied locale is invalid or unsupported.
          in: query
          name: locale
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Alerts"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - alerts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /metadata/dimensions:
    get:
      description: List the metadata for the dimensions available to this AdExchange
        account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.metadata.dimensions.list
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Metadata"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - metadata
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /metadata/metrics:
    get:
      description: List the metadata for the metrics available to this AdExchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.metadata.metrics.list
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Metadata"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - metadata
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /preferreddeals:
    get:
      description: List the preferred deals for this Ad Exchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.preferreddeals.list
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/PreferredDeals"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - preferreddeals
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/preferreddeals/{dealId}":
    get:
      description: Get information about the selected Ad Exchange Preferred Deal.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.preferreddeals.get
      parameters:
        - description: Preferred deal to get information about.
          in: path
          name: dealId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/PreferredDeal"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - preferreddeals
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /reports:
    get:
      description: Generate an Ad Exchange report based on the report request sent in the
        query parameters. Returns the result as JSON; to retrieve output in CSV
        format specify "alt=csv" as a query parameter.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.reports.generate
      parameters:
        - description: Dimensions to base the report on.
          in: query
          name: dimension
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: End of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.
          in: query
          name: endDate
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Filters to be run on the report.
          in: query
          name: filter
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local
            language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.
          in: query
          name: locale
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 50000
        - description: Numeric columns to include in the report.
          in: query
          name: metric
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: The name of a dimension or metric to sort the resulting report on,
            optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort
            descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted
            ascending.
          in: query
          name: sort
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: Start of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format,
            inclusive.
          in: query
          name: startDate
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Index of the first row of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: startIndex
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 5000
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Report"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - reports
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /reports/saved:
    get:
      description: List all saved reports in this Ad Exchange account.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.reports.saved.list
      parameters:
        - description: The maximum number of saved reports to include in the response, used
            for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 100
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through saved reports. To
            retrieve the next page, set this parameter to the value of
            "nextPageToken" from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/SavedReports"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - reports
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/reports/{savedReportId}":
    get:
      description: Generate an Ad Exchange report based on the saved report ID sent in the
        query parameters.
      operationId: adexchangeseller.reports.saved.generate
      parameters:
        - description: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local
            language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.
          in: query
          name: locale
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 50000
        - description: The saved report to retrieve.
          in: path
          name: savedReportId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Index of the first row of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: startIndex
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 5000
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Report"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adexchange.seller.readonly
      tags:
        - reports
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
servers:
  - url: https://www.googleapis.com/adexchangeseller/v1.1
components:
  parameters:
    alt:
      description: Data format for the response.
      in: query
      name: alt
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - csv
          - json
        default: json
    fields:
      description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.
      in: query
      name: fields
      schema:
        type: string
    key:
      description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API
        access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0
        token.
      in: query
      name: key
      schema:
        type: string
    oauth_token:
      description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.
      in: query
      name: oauth_token
      schema:
